<A HREF="http://everquest.station.sony.com/downtime_fs.html"><B>Patch Day Reminder:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Tomorrow (Thursday June 29th) is a big patch day. The servers will be going down at 05:00 Pacific time, and the estimated down time is 8 hours.
</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="tales.html"><B>Norrathian Tales:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Another very well written piece of fiction by Mordier Morvran of Bert! <A HREF="stories/shin_kao.html">Shin Kao</A> continues the adventures of the human rogue as he draws ever closer to the ultimate darkness.</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="main.phtml#1.0 Poll"><B>Polls:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Here are the results from last weeks' poll question <I></I>"If you have the expansion pack, about how often do you play in the new Kunark zones?"</I></FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
1. Always in Kunark   14.99% (116 votes)<BR>
2. Mostly in Kunark   13.44% (104 votes)<BR>
3. About half and half   9.43% (73 votes)<BR>
4. Sometimes in Kunark   8.79% (68 votes)<BR>
5. Seldom in Kunark   53.36% (413 votes)<BR>
<B>-------------------</B><BR>
<B>Total Votes:</B> 774</FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
As you can easily see, the results showed a majority did not play very often in Kunark<BR><BR>

To try and discover why over 50% of the players seldom play in Kunark, I set up this weeks poll to let you choose from the most common complaints mentioned about the expansion continent.</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="maps.php3"><B>Maps:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Another great map from Zealott, this time of Infected Paw. I also added 2 new maps of the Temple of Droga over on EQ Atlas.</FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">1. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Infected%20Paw">Infected Paw</A> - By Zealott of Veeshan</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">2. <A HREF="map_search.php3?action=zone&add_zone=Droga">Temple of Droga</A> - By EQ Atlas</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="files.html"><B>Files:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
For those who like me loved that song "Has Anyone Seen My Corpse?", I just updated it. The original artists who created it, Electric Funstuff, have completely re-mixed it and the new version is now posted. I also added a nice little mapping utility called EQMapper, that lets you create maps using your /loc command and in-game chat logs.</FONT><BR><BR>

<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">1. <A HREF="http://files.loreseekers.com/files/corpse128.mp3">Has Anyone Seen My Corpse?</A> - The Song!</FONT><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">2. <A HREF="http://files.loreseekers.com/files/eqmapper.exe">EQMapper Ver. 2</A> - by Jebo</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="links.html"><B>Links:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
Added a link to a handy new reference site for Alchemy. Visit <A HREF="http://home.elp.rr.com/wolfclan/alchemy/alchemyindex.html" TARGET="_New">Belgar's Ultimate Guide to Alchemy</A>.</FONT><BR><BR>

<A HREF="screenshots.html"><B>Daily Kunark Image:</B></A><BR>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="ARIEL">
We still need more screenshots for our "Kunark Daily Image" on our main page, so if you see a nice sunset, dungeon, beast or castle.... make sure you take a nice picture and <A HREF="mailto:madwand@home.com">mail</A> it to us !
</FONT><BR><BR>

